## 3. Technology & Package Breakdown

If your professors or panel ask "Why did you use this package?", here are your exact answers.

### Frontend (React/Vite) Packages:
| Package | Why we used it (The Purpose) |
| :--- | :--- |
| **`react` & `react-dom`** | The core library for building our component-based user interface. |
| **`react-router-dom`** | To handle client-side routing. It allows users to switch between the Home, Login, and Booking pages instantly without the browser reloading. |
| **`tailwindcss`** | A utility-first CSS framework. It allowed us to rapidly build a highly responsive, modern, and beautiful UI without writing thousands of lines of custom CSS files. |
| **`axios`** | Used to make asynchronous HTTP requests to our Node.js backend API (fetching movies, submitting logins). |
| **`socket.io-client`** | Connects to the backend WebSocket server to listen for real-time seat lock/unlock events. |
| **`recharts`** | A charting library used to build the beautiful data visualization graphs in the Admin Dashboard. |
| **`lucide-react` / `react-icons`** | Provides the crisp, modern SVG icons used throughout the interface. |
| **`html5-qrcode`** | Provides access to the device camera to scan ticket QR codes at the cinema entrance. |
| **`vite`** | Our modern build tool. It replaces Create React App (Webpack) to provide lightning-fast local development and highly optimized production builds. |

### Backend (Node.js/Express) Packages:
| Package | Why we used it (The Purpose) |
| :--- | :--- |
| **`express`** | The core web framework that handles all our API routes (e.g., `/api/movies`, `/api/auth`) and middleware. |
| **`mongoose`** | An Object Data Modeling (ODM) library. It provides a structured schema for our MongoDB data, making it easy to create relationships between Users, Movies, Shows, and Bookings. |
| **`jsonwebtoken` (JWT)** | Used for stateless authentication. When a user logs in, they receive a cryptographic token that securely identifies them on subsequent requests without needing sessions. |
| **`bcryptjs`** | A cryptographic hashing library. We use this to hash user passwords before saving them to MongoDB so that even if the database is breached, user passwords remain secure. |
| **`stripe`** | The official server-side SDK for Stripe. It allows us to securely initiate and verify financial transactions for ticket purchases. |
| **`socket.io`** | The server-side WebSocket engine. It keeps a persistent connection with users to broadcast live seating updates. |
| **`nodemailer`** | Used to send automated emails, such as booking confirmations or password reset OTPs. |
| **`cors`** | A security middleware that allows our frontend (running on one port/domain) to legally request data from our backend API. |
| **`dotenv`** | Loads sensitive environment variables (like our MongoDB URI and Stripe Secret Key) from a `.env` file so they are never hardcoded in the source code. |

